               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440819-name-1151" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1151" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1151" type="surname" value="STEVENS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1151" type="given" value="JANE ANN"></interp>JANE ANN STEVENS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am single. About a quarter-past ten o'clock in the evening, on the 8th of Aug., I was at an exhibition of wax-work in Holborn—I felt a hand in my pocket, where I had a purse and two shillings—I turned, and saw Norman had the purse in his hand—he dropped it on the floor—Bullen was close to him—this is my purse—it was safe in my pocket two minutes before—when Norman had it he was putting his hand across to Bullen.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440819-name-1152" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1152" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1152" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1152" type="given" value="CORNELIUS"></interp>CORNELIUS TAYLOR</persName>
                  </hi>. I am check-taker at the exhibition. On the 8th of Aug. I saw the prosecutrix, about a quarter-past ten o'clock—as the man was going round describing the exhibition, the prisoners came in—they went directly to the prosecutrix—Norman made his way in front of her, and Bullen kept behind her—I saw Bullen put his hand into her pocket—he then got in</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184408190179"></xptr>
               <p>front of her—she said, "You have got my purse"—he said, "I have not, neither did I see it"—I saw him put his hand behind him, and hand it to Norman, who dropped it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Bullen.</hi> I know nothing of it; I was looking at the wax-work, and they took me.</p>
